A middled aged business man ( name withheld) who kidnapped in Ozoro, Isoko North Local Government Area of the State by four armed gunmen has regained freedom. Daily Independent gathered that the victim was waylaid by four armed men was kidnapped and taken away in the boot of his Lexus car with Reg. No. ASB 124 HK. It was gathered that the kidnappers drove their victim from Ozoro to Ughelli in Ughelli North LGA where they met their waterloo. It was gathered that the DPO of Ozoro who received an information about the incident deployed the Dragon Patrol in search of the victim. It was revealed that the police team went on an intelligent led operation and trailed the kidnappers to PTI junction Effurun, where the kidnappers upon noticing that the teams were closing in on them abandoned the victim and the vehicle and fled. The victim (name withheld) ‘m’ age 22yrs of Ozoro was rescued unhurt and the vehicle recovered. While the police has declared a manhunt to arrest the fleeing hoodlums. In a related development, a member of a drug dealing gang identified as Sajor Louis. POLL It was gathered that the suspect was nabbed during a raid of black spot in 74 area, Asaba. It was learnt that the suspect was arrested and ninety-one (91) wraps of weeds suspected to be Indian hemp, one hundred and twenty four (124) wraps of loud, fifty (50) parcels of SK, some razlers and some bottles of liquid mixed with substance suspected to be Indian hemp were recovered. It was also gathered that investigation is going to arrests other fleeing members of drug gang. Commissioner of Police, Delta State, Ali Mohammed Ari warned that the state would not be a place for daredevil criminals.